%N A218420 Number of n X 2 binary arrays with every 0 a horizontal, vertical or antidiagonal neighbor to some 1.
%H A218420 R. H. Hardin, <a href="/A218420/b218420.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..210</a>
%H A218420 <a href="/index/Rec#order_05">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (3,3,1,1,1).
%F A218420 Empirical: a(n) = 3*a(n-1) + 3*a(n-2) + a(n-3) + a(n-4) + a(n-5).
%F A218420 Empirical g.f.: x*(3 + 4*x + x^2 + 2*x^3 + x^4) / (1 - 3*x - 3*x^2 - x^3 - x^4 - x^5). - _Colin Barker_, Mar 10 2018
%F A218420 The above empirical formulas confirmed using the transfer matrix method. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 15 2026
